{
  "stem": "1753.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 205.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the-- the-- the Ukrainians, I suppose it's known just about to most people, these are the Ukrainians that were part of the Russian army in 1941 when a division of 40,000 Russian soldiers, under the direction of General [?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Vlasov, ?] [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] ran away from the Russians and went over to the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave themselves up because Ukraine, as we even know more so today, they weren't so in love with the Russians themselves.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there were a lot of ethnic Germans in the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they-- these were most of the guards in many of the camps throughout Poland and other areas, in particular.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So now there was-- we have the uprising.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We got back into the-- into our camp, Treblinka I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We learned what was going on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Again, they lined us up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Many of the prisoners and workers that were left behind, most of them, were done away with.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The group that came back from [INAUDIBLE] or [INAUDIBLE] respectively, was a new selection, because they were trimming the [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] prisoners to absolute limit, limited group, to 550.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the morning, there were 3,000 some odd.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before the day was over, part of the ones that were done away with before we returned from work, and additional ones that came from the work detail that spent the day in-- working on the railroads.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Was again a selection.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, fortunately for me, myself and another young gentleman, about-- a young man about my age, by the name of David Taup from Berlin, we were selected to be water carriers, which was a very important post.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The water carriers before, they were involved in the uprising, made duplicate keys to the gun chambers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
